description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to be involved in crucial laboratory work testing for COVID 19 with our existing enthusiastic and dedicated team. An excellent opportunity for those with an interest in science and laboratory medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential requirements are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 3 in a relevant subject (e.g science)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience of working in a clinical laboratory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;technically competent of performing a wide range of laboratory procedures and tasks that require precision and manual dexterity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;knowledge and experience of health and safety practices relevant to clinical microbiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience of UKAS accreditation to ISO 15189 standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to produce accurate and reliable data in all aspects of laboratory work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is to support Coronavirus testing for Lancashire and South Cumbria. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to work flexibly on a planned shift pattern to cover a 24/7 working pattern&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shifts will be scheduled and planned in advance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: Tuesday 24th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Robert Bolton, Point of Care Manager - robert.bolton@lthtr.nhs.uk or 01772 523007&lt;/p&gt;
